WEBVTT

00:01.835 --> 00:03.920
(muted chatter)

00:06.798 --> 00:09.676
-(chatter fading in)
-(sighs)

00:12.178 --> 00:13.805
HOST:
Right this way.

00:13.888 --> 00:15.807
WOMAN:
The octopus salad is amazing.

00:15.890 --> 00:18.101
("Days Like This" by MorMor
playing)

00:18.184 --> 00:22.772
♪<i> But you can't help</i>
<i>but feel alone</i> ♪

00:22.856 --> 00:24.107
(laughter)

00:24.190 --> 00:27.652
♪<i> You don't need a reason why</i> ♪

00:29.404 --> 00:33.408
♪<i> Hold your head</i>
<i>and carry on...</i> ♪

00:34.701 --> 00:35.952
So, I was thinking
we could just get

00:36.035 --> 00:37.328
a bunch of little things
and share?

00:37.412 --> 00:41.499
That way we can try
everything tapas-style.

00:41.583 --> 00:42.625
Don't know
what half this stuff is.

00:42.709 --> 00:44.419
I've been wanting to come
to this place for months.

00:44.502 --> 00:46.087
What?

00:46.171 --> 00:48.006
Ever since Clara Bordeaux
won <i> Chef Boss,</i>

00:48.089 --> 00:51.217
it's, like, impossible
to get in here.

00:53.052 --> 00:54.971
-What is it?
-Hmm?

00:55.054 --> 00:57.932
Well, you, you're looking
at me weird.

00:58.016 --> 00:59.434
Oh, am I? I'm sorry.

00:59.517 --> 01:01.144
Sorry.

01:01.227 --> 01:04.188
Anyway, she won last season
of <i> Chef Boss,</i> and...

01:04.272 --> 01:06.316
It's just, your hair.

01:06.399 --> 01:07.942
(stammers)
What about my hair?

01:08.026 --> 01:11.488
It's... it's curly.

01:11.571 --> 01:13.490
Uh...

01:13.573 --> 01:16.493
I feel like,
in your profile photo, it was...

01:16.576 --> 01:19.370
I feel like it was straight.

01:20.580 --> 01:22.707
-(chuckles softly)
-Um...

01:22.791 --> 01:24.000
Okay.

01:24.083 --> 01:25.168
(chuckles)
It's not that curly.

01:25.251 --> 01:27.003
-See? Uh, straight.
-Mm-hmm.

01:27.086 --> 01:29.547
Uh... curly.

01:30.715 --> 01:32.175
I wear it both ways.

01:32.258 --> 01:33.718
-Okay.
-(chuckles softly)

01:33.802 --> 01:35.845
Do you not like it,
or something?

01:38.056 --> 01:40.266
Yeah, it's fine.

01:43.102 --> 01:44.813
(both clear throats)

01:44.896 --> 01:48.149
So, I read on Yelp
that the squid ink paella

01:48.233 --> 01:50.026
is a must, so...

01:50.109 --> 01:52.237
<i>-ANNIE: Hello?</i>
-I'm really not crazy about...

01:52.320 --> 01:54.697
I'm sorry.
What-what did you just say?

01:54.781 --> 01:56.908
That the squid ink paella
is a must.

01:56.991 --> 01:59.035
<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>Hello?</i>

01:59.118 --> 02:01.120
♪ ♪

02:07.836 --> 02:08.586
Ooh, and do you like croquettes?

02:08.669 --> 02:09.838
'Cause they've got pork
or chicken.

02:09.920 --> 02:12.215
<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>Is someone there?</i>

02:12.298 --> 02:14.884
<i>PHIL:</i>
<i>Um, hello?</i>

02:14.968 --> 02:17.345
<i>(Annie gasps)</i>

02:17.428 --> 02:20.056
{\an5}<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>Wait, wait,</i>
<i>you can actually hear me?</i>

02:20.139 --> 02:22.517
<i>PHIL:</i>
<i>What is... what's going on?</i>

02:22.600 --> 02:24.018
<i>-This can't be real.</i>
-Uh, if that's okay with you,

02:24.102 --> 02:25.228
I'm gonna get chicken.
And it comes with four,

02:25.311 --> 02:27.272
so we could each get two.

02:27.355 --> 02:29.357
Yeah?

02:29.440 --> 02:30.567
Are you okay?

02:30.650 --> 02:31.943
Hmm? Hmm?

02:32.026 --> 02:33.736
Uh...

02:33.820 --> 02:35.822
I... am fine. I'm fine.

02:35.905 --> 02:38.032
<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>How are you doing this?</i>

02:38.116 --> 02:40.243
{\an5}<i>-PHIL: Stop. Stop it. Stop it.</i>
-Uh, so maybe not
the croquettes, then?

02:40.326 --> 02:43.121
<i>-Stop it. S-Stop it.</i>
-Unless you want them.

02:43.204 --> 02:46.249
{\an8}<i>-Stop it. Stop it.</i>
<i>-ANNIE: Oh, my God.</i>
<i>What is happening?</i>

02:46.332 --> 02:48.251
{\an8}-So you do...
<i>-PHIL: I don't understand.</i>
<i>Can you hear me?</i>

02:48.334 --> 02:51.713
{\an5}<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>Yes. Of course I can hear you.</i>
<i>I'm talking to you.</i>

02:51.796 --> 02:54.257
<i>Or I'm thinking at you,</i>
<i>I guess. What is happening?</i>

02:54.340 --> 02:57.260
{\an5}<i>-Is that what's happening?</i>
-I have no fucking clue.
-Excuse me?

02:57.343 --> 02:58.887
{\an8}<i>-ANNIE: Are you still there?</i>
-What? No. I'm sorry.

02:58.970 --> 03:00.555
-What? That wasn't for you.
<i>-Hello?</i>

03:00.638 --> 03:02.056
<i>-(high-pitched ringing)</i>
-JULIA: Okay.

03:02.140 --> 03:03.391
-Look, if you don't want them...
-Yes. Yes. Yes.

03:03.474 --> 03:04.851
{\an8}<i>-ANNIE: Hello?</i>
-Yes.

03:04.934 --> 03:06.603
{\an8}Okay, you're not listening,
are you, Phil?

03:06.686 --> 03:07.896
{\an8}<i>-ANNIE: Hello?</i>
-Okay.

03:07.979 --> 03:09.147
{\an8}Yeah, okay.

03:09.230 --> 03:11.190
Hey.
Hey, hey, could you excuse me

03:11.274 --> 03:13.610
for just one moment?

03:13.693 --> 03:16.279
Uh... yeah.

03:16.362 --> 03:18.031
Shit.

03:24.537 --> 03:25.747
(panting)

03:25.830 --> 03:27.457
<i>PHIL:</i>
<i>Am I going crazy?</i>

03:29.375 --> 03:33.546
{\an5}<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>If you're going crazy,</i>
<i>then I-I guess I am, too.</i>

03:35.381 --> 03:38.134
Okay.

03:38.217 --> 03:39.802
Ha-ha.

03:39.886 --> 03:41.846
This is...

03:41.930 --> 03:43.973
This is very funny-- Uh...

03:46.017 --> 03:47.644
<i>Who is this?</i>
<i>Get out of my head.</i>

03:47.727 --> 03:51.105
<i>-ANNIE: You get out of my head.</i>
-No, you get out!

03:51.189 --> 03:53.274
{\an5}<i>PHIL:</i>
<i>What are you, some-- are you</i>
<i>some kind of psychic?</i>

03:53.358 --> 03:57.487
{\an5}<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>No! I was just, I was just</i>
<i>minding my own business at home</i>

03:57.570 --> 03:59.530
<i>and your voice just suddenly</i>
<i>popped into my head.</i>

03:59.614 --> 04:02.158
<i>PHIL:</i>
<i>Oh, no, no, no, no-- Okay.</i>

04:02.241 --> 04:04.661
<i>-You listen to me.</i>
<i>-ANNIE: I am listening to you.</i>

04:04.744 --> 04:06.788
{\an5}<i>PHIL:</i>
<i>Whatever the hell this is,</i>
<i>I don't like it.</i>

04:06.871 --> 04:09.624
{\an5}<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>(chuckles)</i> You <i> don't like this?</i>
<i>I don't like this!</i>

04:09.707 --> 04:11.834
<i>PHIL:</i>
<i>Great, so stop talking to me.</i>

04:11.918 --> 04:13.753
<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>And you stop talking to me.</i>

04:13.836 --> 04:15.505
<i>-PHIL: Deal!</i>
<i>-ANNIE: Deal!</i>

04:17.048 --> 04:19.050
(piano music playing quietly)

04:31.479 --> 04:34.857
{\an5}NARRATOR:
A voice in your head can mean
a few different things.

04:34.941 --> 04:37.902
A conscience,
divine inspiration...

04:39.904 --> 04:42.198
...or madness.

04:42.281 --> 04:46.536
But what if, instead, it were
a case of crossed wires,

04:46.619 --> 04:51.332
one made through the tangled,
enigmatic switchboards

04:51.416 --> 04:53.584
of The Twilight Zone?

04:55.628 --> 04:57.046
<i>(The Twilight Zone</i> theme
playing)

04:57.130 --> 04:58.840
<i>NARRATOR: You're traveling</i>
<i>through another dimension,</i>

04:58.923 --> 05:01.884
<i>a dimension not only of</i>
<i>sight and sound but of mind.</i>

05:01.968 --> 05:05.096
<i>It is the middle ground</i>
<i>between light and shadow,</i>

05:05.179 --> 05:07.890
<i>between science</i>
<i>and superstition.</i>

05:07.974 --> 05:10.435
{\an8}<i>And it lies between</i>
<i>the pit of one's fears</i>

05:10.518 --> 05:13.688
{\an8}<i>and the summit</i>
<i>of one's knowledge.</i>

05:13.771 --> 05:16.524
<i>You are now traveling through</i>
<i>a dimension of imagination.</i>

05:16.607 --> 05:20.862
<i>You've just crossed over</i>
<i>into The Twilight Zone.</i>

05:35.334 --> 05:37.336
<i>PHIL:</i>
<i>Um...</i>

05:38.337 --> 05:41.257
<i>Are you there?</i>

05:41.340 --> 05:43.551
-(exhales)
<i>-ANNIE: Yep.</i>

05:45.511 --> 05:46.929
<i>PHIL:</i>
<i>So, then I told her</i>

05:47.013 --> 05:50.016
to get out, but this morning
she's still here.

05:50.099 --> 05:52.435
-"She" being the voice?
-Yeah.

05:52.518 --> 05:56.272
Hmm. How did the rest of
your date go last night?

05:56.355 --> 05:58.483
(stammers)
As expected. Shitty.

05:58.566 --> 06:00.568
You know,
I dropped 200 bucks for nothing.

06:00.651 --> 06:02.111
It's not a transaction.

06:02.195 --> 06:03.738
No, of course not,
I don't want a transaction.

06:03.821 --> 06:07.575
{\an8}I want something meaningful
with someone awesome.

06:07.658 --> 06:08.785
{\an8}(exhales)

06:08.868 --> 06:10.787
{\an8}Mm-hmm.

06:10.870 --> 06:12.914
{\an8}I want to go back to this voice
that you heard.

06:12.997 --> 06:17.335
{\an8}Can we discuss the possibility

06:17.418 --> 06:20.004
{\an8}that the voice was perhaps you?

06:21.506 --> 06:22.965
{\an8}Well, we spend a lot of time

06:23.049 --> 06:26.427
{\an8}in here talking about how
you're "doomed to be alone,"

06:26.511 --> 06:31.099
{\an8}and how all these women, e-every
date you bring up, in fact,

06:31.182 --> 06:33.935
{\an8}-you say it's their fault
that you're unhappy.
-Okay.

06:34.018 --> 06:35.812
{\an8}So, can we discuss
the possibility

06:35.895 --> 06:38.981
{\an8}that this voice could,
in fact, be a coping mechanism?

06:39.065 --> 06:41.109
{\an8}A fabrication that you made up
to get out of a date

06:41.192 --> 06:44.070
{\an8}that you knew wasn't
gonna go any further?

06:44.153 --> 06:45.613
{\an8}PHIL: I-It wasn't going
any further regardless, okay?

06:45.696 --> 06:47.824
{\an8}She was vapid, she was boring.

06:47.907 --> 06:49.909
{\an8}Her hair...

06:51.536 --> 06:53.287
{\an8}-It was different, but...
-It's okay, Phil.

06:53.371 --> 06:56.290
{\an8}It's okay to have
high standards,

06:56.374 --> 06:59.293
{\an8}but life isn't
a romantic comedy.

06:59.377 --> 07:03.005
{\an8}And the perfect woman
doesn't exist. So...

07:03.089 --> 07:05.299
{\an8}maybe you and I can come up
with some strategies

07:05.383 --> 07:07.969
{\an8}-so you can compromise.
-She could've compromised.

07:08.052 --> 07:10.346
{\an8}"She" being the voice
or your date?

07:10.429 --> 07:12.181
{\an8}Well, the voice and I
actually made a deal

07:12.265 --> 07:13.599
{\an8}to stop talking to each other.

07:13.683 --> 07:16.519
{\an8}That's a, that's a compromise,
isn't it?

07:16.602 --> 07:18.688
{\an8}Yeah.

07:21.899 --> 07:24.360
{\an8}Philip, are you familiar
with the term

07:24.443 --> 07:26.279
{\an8}dissociative identity disorder?

07:27.613 --> 07:29.532
{\an8}You might have heard of it
referred to

07:29.615 --> 07:31.576
{\an8}as multiple
personality disorder.

07:31.659 --> 07:33.035
{\an8}What, are you telling me
I'm crazy?

07:33.119 --> 07:35.037
{\an8}No, that's not what I'm saying.

07:35.121 --> 07:37.415
{\an8}Yes, Doctor, I have some
anxiety, and who doesn't have

07:37.498 --> 07:40.376
{\an8}a little existential dread
these days? But come on.

07:40.459 --> 07:42.503
{\an8}(fading):
Yes, you're right. Anxiety...

07:42.587 --> 07:44.714
{\an8}<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>I'm bored.</i>

07:44.797 --> 07:46.507
{\an8}<i>-What are you up to?</i>
-There she is.

07:46.591 --> 07:48.509
{\an8}She is talking to me.
She is talking to me right now.

07:48.593 --> 07:50.386
{\an8}<i>This is not a good time.</i>
<i>Okay? My shrink</i>

07:50.469 --> 07:51.554
{\an8}<i>is currently telling me</i>
<i>that I'm...</i>

07:51.637 --> 07:52.930
{\an8}<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>Let me guess, that you're nuts?</i>

07:53.014 --> 07:54.932
{\an8}THERAPIST:
And what's she saying?

07:55.016 --> 07:56.976
{\an8}That you think I'm crazy.

07:57.059 --> 07:58.436
{\an8}<i>Oh, here it comes.</i>

07:59.478 --> 08:01.189
{\an8}Philip,

08:01.272 --> 08:05.318
{\an8}the symptoms of dissociative
identity disorder often overlap

08:05.401 --> 08:07.862
{\an8}-with a number of...
<i>-PHIL: Well, now she definitely</i>
<i>thinks I'm nuts.</i>

08:07.945 --> 08:09.697
{\an8}<i>That is just great.</i>
<i>Thank you so much.</i>

08:09.780 --> 08:11.073
{\an8}<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>Hey, you're the one</i>

08:11.157 --> 08:12.533
{\an8}<i>who checked in with me</i>
<i>this morning.</i>

08:12.617 --> 08:14.452
{\an8}<i>What happened to our deal, huh?</i>

08:14.535 --> 08:15.870
{\an8}<i>PHIL: Look, I wasn't trying</i>
<i>to start a conversation</i>

08:15.953 --> 08:16.787
{\an8}<i>in the middle of therapy.</i>

08:16.871 --> 08:20.124
{\an8}<i>ANNIE: Well, I'm sorry</i>
<i>for being bored.</i>

08:20.208 --> 08:22.126
{\an8}<i>-You know what's funny, though?</i>
<i>-PHIL: Huh?</i>

08:22.210 --> 08:23.961
{\an8}<i>ANNIE: My shrink tried</i>
<i>to tell me the same thing</i>

08:24.045 --> 08:25.755
{\an8}<i>when I told her about you.</i>
<i>God, what quacks.</i>

08:25.838 --> 08:27.548
{\an8}<i>PHIL: Totally. Actually--</i>
<i>She doesn't even know</i>

08:27.632 --> 08:29.634
{\an8}<i>I stopped listening to her,</i>
<i>like, a minute ago.</i>

08:29.717 --> 08:31.594
{\an8}<i>-(Annie chuckles)</i>
<i>-That is, that is not</i>
<i>an expert.</i>

08:31.677 --> 08:34.639
{\an8}<i>ANNIE: Mm-mm. Yeah,</i>
<i>they're real experts</i>

08:34.722 --> 08:36.057
{\an8}<i>at telling us</i>
<i>what's wrong with us.</i>

08:36.140 --> 08:37.767
{\an8}<i>How's this for a diagnosis?</i>

08:37.850 --> 08:40.227
{\an8}<i>My life is shitty,</i>
<i>therefore I feel like shit.</i>

08:40.311 --> 08:43.898
{\an8}<i>PHIL (laughs):</i>
<i>Uh-huh. Yeah.</i>

08:43.981 --> 08:46.108
{\an8}<i>You're right.</i>
<i>I don't have to listen to this.</i>

08:46.192 --> 08:48.069
{\an8}<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>You sure don't.</i>

08:48.152 --> 08:50.196
{\an8}And the only way they know how
to deal with it is by cutting

08:50.279 --> 08:51.781
{\an8}off from their thoughts
and their feelings.

08:51.864 --> 08:53.074
{\an8}It's almost like they're
watching themselves,

08:53.157 --> 08:54.075
{\an8}like they're watch...

08:54.158 --> 08:56.160
{\an8}-(grunts)
-Philip?

08:57.370 --> 08:58.579
{\an8}Are you okay?

09:00.164 --> 09:01.499
{\an8}<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>Holy crap.</i>

09:01.582 --> 09:03.376
{\an8}<i>Did you actually leave</i>

09:03.459 --> 09:05.419
{\an8}<i>-in the middle of a session?</i>
<i>-PHIL: I did.</i>

09:05.503 --> 09:08.464
{\an8}<i>-Yeah, I did that.</i>
<i>-Wow.</i>

09:08.548 --> 09:09.924
{\an8}<i>ANNIE: I would pay money</i>
<i>to see her face</i>

09:10.007 --> 09:11.759
{\an8}<i>when you walked out that door.</i>

09:11.842 --> 09:13.928
{\an8}<i>PHIL: Okay, all right,</i>
<i>look, whoever you are,</i>

09:14.011 --> 09:15.763
{\an8}<i>this is freakin' weird.</i>

09:15.846 --> 09:17.306
{\an8}<i>You're just here,</i>
<i>spying on me all the time.</i>

09:17.390 --> 09:18.849
{\an8}<i>My thoughts are private, okay?</i>

09:18.933 --> 09:20.434
{\an8}<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>God, don't flatter yourself.</i>

09:20.518 --> 09:21.811
{\an8}<i>You're not</i>
<i>that interesting, pal.</i>

09:21.894 --> 09:23.896
{\an8}<i>PHIL:</i>
<i>Ugh.</i>

09:39.578 --> 09:43.708
{\an8}♪<i> Back in '89</i>
<i>we'd say adieu...</i> ♪

09:43.791 --> 09:45.501
{\an8}<i>PHIL:</i>
<i>Psst. Hey.</i>

09:45.584 --> 09:48.170
{\an8}<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>Oh, my God. What do you want?</i>

09:48.254 --> 09:52.550
{\an8}<i>PHIL: Uh, can you, like...</i>
<i>see what I see?</i>

09:52.633 --> 09:54.176
{\an8}<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>What? No.</i>

09:54.260 --> 09:56.679
{\an8}<i>-Wait, can you see what I see?</i>
<i>-PHIL: No.</i>

09:56.762 --> 09:58.055
{\an8}<i>-No. No.</i>
<i>-ANNIE: Oh, good.</i>

09:58.139 --> 09:59.682
{\an8}<i>PHIL:</i>
<i>But, okay, so you can't,</i>

09:59.765 --> 10:02.310
{\an8}<i>like, hear what I'm feeling</i>
<i>or anything?</i>

10:02.393 --> 10:04.395
{\an8}<i>Did you basically sense me</i>
<i>looking at that barista?</i>

10:04.478 --> 10:06.355
{\an8}<i>ANNIE: Oh, my God. Were you</i>
<i>just ogling some chick?</i>

10:06.439 --> 10:07.523
{\an8}<i>PHIL:</i>
<i>No, no, no, no, that's not...</i>

10:07.606 --> 10:09.317
{\an8}<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>Oh, yeah, I can hear</i>

10:09.400 --> 10:10.818
{\an8}<i>all your disgusting thoughts...</i>

10:10.901 --> 10:12.194
{\an8}<i>-PHIL: Oh, come on.</i>
<i>-...you perv.</i>

10:12.278 --> 10:14.238
<i>-No, I-I swear...</i>
<i>-ANNIE: Relax.</i>

10:14.322 --> 10:18.159
<i>I can only hear</i>
<i>when you're thinking at me.</i>

10:18.242 --> 10:20.369
<i>Your voice just kind of pops</i>
<i>into my head.</i>

10:20.453 --> 10:22.038
<i>Besides, I have</i>
<i>better things to do</i>

10:22.121 --> 10:23.998
<i>than police</i>
<i>your pervy thoughts.</i>

10:24.081 --> 10:27.376
<i>PHIL:</i>
<i>Okay. Cool.</i>

10:27.460 --> 10:31.130
{\an5}<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>But who's this barista?</i>
<i>You should ask her out.</i>

10:31.213 --> 10:34.050
♪<i> We got along...</i> ♪

10:34.133 --> 10:36.719
<i>PHIL:</i>
<i>Don't you tell me what to do.</i>

10:36.802 --> 10:38.220
<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>Oh, come on, be bold.</i>

10:38.304 --> 10:40.723
<i>Go after what you want.</i>

10:40.806 --> 10:42.725
{\an5}<i>-Uh, there's no way.</i>
<i>I wouldn't have a shot.</i>
<i>-Do it!</i>

10:42.808 --> 10:43.726
<i>-Do it!</i>
<i>-Come on, no.</i>

10:43.809 --> 10:45.102
<i>-Do it!</i>
<i>-Okay.</i>

10:46.645 --> 10:48.105
-Hey.
-Hey.

10:48.189 --> 10:49.690
I haven't seen you in a while.

10:49.774 --> 10:51.067
How are you?

