19:54.860 --> 19:58.113
why I exist.

19:58.196 --> 20:00.073
What's my purpose?

20:00.157 --> 20:02.451
{\an5}<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>Phil, all of us are here</i>
<i>for a reason.</i>

20:02.534 --> 20:04.328
<i>Including you.</i>

20:04.411 --> 20:07.623
<i>Call it fate or whatever,</i>
<i>but nothing's random.</i>

20:07.706 --> 20:10.292
<i>Like this connection we have,</i>

20:10.375 --> 20:13.962
<i>there's got to be</i>
<i>a reason for it, right?</i>

20:14.046 --> 20:15.797
It just freaks me out.

20:15.881 --> 20:18.342
I'm not...

20:18.425 --> 20:21.053
not particularly successful.

20:23.055 --> 20:24.806
Like talented or...

20:24.890 --> 20:26.350
(sniffles)

20:26.433 --> 20:29.478
...alpha-male hot.

20:29.561 --> 20:33.315
I'm just not special
in any way, you know?

20:33.398 --> 20:35.692
So...

20:35.776 --> 20:37.653
why am I here?

20:37.736 --> 20:39.780
<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>Phil?</i>

20:39.863 --> 20:41.990
{\an8}<i>Even if we don't totally</i>
<i>understand what the hell</i>

20:42.074 --> 20:44.451
{\an8}<i>we're doing with our lives,</i>
<i>one day,</i>

20:44.534 --> 20:47.204
{\an8}<i>we'll look back and we'll see</i>
<i>we were following our path.</i>

20:47.287 --> 20:49.331
{\an8}<i>(sighs)</i>

20:49.414 --> 20:51.500
<i>With the way things are</i>
<i>in my life right now,</i>

20:51.583 --> 20:54.294
<i>if I didn't believe there was</i>
<i>something better out there</i>

20:54.378 --> 20:57.005
<i>for me, like, I don't know,</i>
<i>an escape hatch</i>

20:57.089 --> 20:58.799
<i>to happiness or something,</i>

20:58.882 --> 21:02.719
<i>I couldn't get out of bed</i>
<i>in the morning.</i>

21:02.803 --> 21:06.974
<i>Phil, I promise you,</i>
<i>you do have a purpose.</i>

21:09.267 --> 21:11.353
(quietly):
Oh, man, I...

21:11.436 --> 21:13.313
I have to be at work
in three hours,

21:13.397 --> 21:15.148
but I just don't want
to hang up.

21:15.232 --> 21:17.651
{\an5}<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>Me neither.</i>
<i>I don't want to be alone.</i>

21:17.734 --> 21:18.694
Mm-mm.

21:18.777 --> 21:21.196
<i>Be with me, Phil.</i>

21:21.279 --> 21:23.824
<i>Touch me, Phil.</i>

21:31.748 --> 21:33.166
<i>PHIL:</i>
<i>Oh, Annie.</i>

21:33.250 --> 21:35.669
<i>(moans softly)</i>

21:38.588 --> 21:40.590
(engine starts outside)

21:45.929 --> 21:48.598
(sighs)

21:50.976 --> 21:54.312
(yawns)

21:56.481 --> 21:58.275
(sighs)

22:00.152 --> 22:02.237
Annie.

22:02.320 --> 22:04.823
My God, these past few weeks,
they've--

22:04.906 --> 22:07.075
they've been the best weeks
of my life.

22:07.159 --> 22:08.869
(laughs)

22:08.952 --> 22:13.290
You're like-- you're everything
I've ever been looking for.

22:13.373 --> 22:15.250
I have to meet you, like, today.

22:15.333 --> 22:18.045
{\an5}<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>Phil, I never meant for things</i>
<i>to get this far.</i>

22:18.128 --> 22:19.713
<i>We're in too deep.</i>

22:19.796 --> 22:21.465
<i>I need it to stop, Phil.</i>

22:21.548 --> 22:23.717
Annie, no. Annie...

22:23.800 --> 22:27.054
Um, I know you feel this,
too, so...

22:27.137 --> 22:29.306
<i>It's too dangerous for me.</i>

22:32.559 --> 22:35.103
This is special.
You s-- you said so.

22:35.187 --> 22:38.231
<i>It's dangerous.</i>
<i>I-I can't do this anymore.</i>

22:38.315 --> 22:39.775
<i>I'm sorry, Phil, I can't.</i>

22:39.858 --> 22:41.943
Uh, Annie, wait. Just plea...

22:42.027 --> 22:44.488
Annie...

22:44.571 --> 22:46.615
Annie!

22:57.000 --> 22:59.002
(gasps)

23:00.045 --> 23:01.713
Annie?

23:09.679 --> 23:11.681
♪ ♪

23:27.030 --> 23:29.366
♪ ♪

23:45.590 --> 23:47.008
♪ ♪

23:50.887 --> 23:53.181
{\an5}<i>PHIL:</i>
<i>Oh, God. Have you seen</i>
<i>this garbage trailer</i>

23:53.265 --> 23:55.183
<i>for the new</i> Deadstick 2 <i> movie?</i>
<i>It's like they--</i>

23:55.267 --> 23:58.645
<i>they're-they're</i>
<i>not even trying anymore.</i>

23:58.728 --> 24:00.564
<i>(sighs)</i>

24:03.400 --> 24:04.818
Oh, what the hell?
You can't even respond to me

24:04.901 --> 24:06.528
like a, like a human being?!

24:06.611 --> 24:09.865
I get it, dude! You're married!
I'm just trying to be friendly!

24:09.948 --> 24:11.867
You don't have to be
such a bitch!

24:11.950 --> 24:14.828
(exhales)

24:17.873 --> 24:19.457
I'm sorry.

24:21.459 --> 24:23.879
I'm sorry, I just miss you.

24:31.469 --> 24:33.638
♪ ♪

24:55.827 --> 24:58.413
(muttering):
Come on, no, no.

24:58.496 --> 25:01.791
(breathing heavily)

25:03.793 --> 25:04.711
WOMAN:
Hello?

25:04.794 --> 25:08.340
(gasping)
Annie?

25:09.341 --> 25:11.343
Annie?

25:11.426 --> 25:13.553
WOMAN:
Hello, Phil?

25:13.637 --> 25:15.722
It's Mrs. King.

25:17.849 --> 25:20.894
(panting)

25:29.069 --> 25:30.862
(TV playing indistinctly nearby)

25:30.946 --> 25:32.781
Third of the month.

25:32.864 --> 25:34.658
Rent is due.

25:34.741 --> 25:37.285
Yeah. Yeah, I'll get back...

25:37.369 --> 25:38.912
I'll get back to you later.

25:42.374 --> 25:45.043
(breathing heavily)

25:52.050 --> 25:54.302
(gasps)

25:54.386 --> 25:56.638
Hey. Hey.

25:58.890 --> 26:01.851
Hey, I just need to know
that this was real.

26:04.437 --> 26:06.314
That you were real.

26:09.359 --> 26:11.861
Please, just say something...

26:11.945 --> 26:14.114
to me and I will...

26:14.197 --> 26:16.491
I'll leave you alone forever,
just say some...

26:16.574 --> 26:19.160
Please, please, please, please.

26:26.793 --> 26:30.088
So, you have, uh, two cats, huh?

26:31.423 --> 26:33.008
Nope.

26:33.091 --> 26:36.136
You sure?
I remember you saying...

26:36.219 --> 26:39.180
saying something
about having two, two cats.

26:40.223 --> 26:42.142
Yeah, I-I definitely didn't.

26:42.225 --> 26:44.811
I'm allergic, so...

26:44.894 --> 26:46.354
(whispers):
I feel like you did.

26:48.064 --> 26:50.066
(sighs)

26:53.069 --> 26:57.365
Um, where did you say
you were from, again?

26:57.449 --> 26:59.034
Uh, here.

26:59.117 --> 27:01.870
Oh, wow, like the,
the city proper?

27:01.953 --> 27:03.663
Mm-hmm.

27:03.747 --> 27:06.875
I never meet anyone
who's actually from Ashford.

27:06.958 --> 27:08.460
You know, everyone claims
they're from Ashford,

27:08.543 --> 27:12.881
but they're really from
Beaver Crest or wherever.

27:12.964 --> 27:14.507
You know,
Florida's the opposite.

27:14.591 --> 27:15.925
Nobody wants to admit
they're from Florida.

27:16.009 --> 27:17.427
<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>Phil?</i>

27:17.510 --> 27:19.095
<i>PHIL:</i>
<i>Annie?</i>

27:19.179 --> 27:21.348
{\an5}<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>Oh, my God, it's so good</i>
<i>to hear your voice!</i>

27:21.431 --> 27:22.557
<i>PHIL:</i>
<i>Oh, God, Annie!</i>

27:22.640 --> 27:23.725
<i>Annie, oh, I miss you so much.</i>

27:23.808 --> 27:25.226
<i>Life sucks without you.</i>

27:25.310 --> 27:26.603
<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>Oh, my God, I've been--</i>

27:26.686 --> 27:28.355
<i>barely been able to get</i>
<i>out of bed.</i>

27:28.438 --> 27:30.398
<i>I'm a total wreck,</i>
<i>but-but these last few weeks</i>

27:30.482 --> 27:32.025
<i>without you have</i>
<i>got me thinking,</i>

27:32.108 --> 27:33.735
<i>and-and here's the thing, Phil:</i>
<i>I need you.</i>

27:33.818 --> 27:35.362
<i>-(Phil sighs)</i>
<i>-Let's do it.</i>

27:35.445 --> 27:36.988
<i>-PHIL: Do what?</i>
<i>-Let's meet, like you said.</i>

27:37.072 --> 27:38.823
<i>PHIL:</i>
<i>Wait. Y-You're serious?</i>

27:38.907 --> 27:40.575
<i>-ANNIE: Yes!</i>
<i>-Wh-What about your husband?</i>

27:40.658 --> 27:43.119
{\an5}<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>I'm tired of waiting.</i>
<i>I'm ready for my life to begin,</i>

27:43.203 --> 27:44.788
<i>and it, and it can't happen</i>
<i>without you.</i>

27:44.871 --> 27:48.083
Oh, my God!
That is the best news ever!

27:48.166 --> 27:51.753
(diners murmuring)

27:51.836 --> 27:54.255
{\an5}<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>Halfway between where I am</i>
<i>and where you are</i>

27:54.339 --> 27:56.091
<i>is exactly in Pilson Bay.</i>

27:56.174 --> 27:57.550
<i>Come meet me, Phil.</i>

27:57.634 --> 27:58.927
<i>Let's meet in the middle.</i>

27:59.010 --> 28:00.470
(laughs softly)

28:00.553 --> 28:03.431
♪<i> You were made for me</i> ♪

28:03.515 --> 28:08.561
♪<i> And nothing more</i> ♪

28:08.645 --> 28:11.940
♪<i> Guided by your voice</i> ♪

28:12.023 --> 28:16.611
♪<i> I see the shore</i> ♪

28:16.694 --> 28:20.407
♪<i> Yeah, the papers</i>
<i>can't report</i> ♪

28:20.490 --> 28:24.619
♪<i> What they don't know</i> ♪

28:24.702 --> 28:28.665
♪<i> So I'll be all the seasons</i> ♪

28:28.748 --> 28:32.961
♪<i> Till I'm fall</i> ♪

28:33.044 --> 28:35.213
♪<i> If you run away...</i> ♪

28:35.296 --> 28:37.507
{\an5}<i>PHIL:</i>
<i>I can't believe that in exactly</i>
<i>four hours and 12 minutes,</i>

28:37.590 --> 28:39.217
<i>I get to finally see your face.</i>

28:39.300 --> 28:40.635
{\an5}<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>I feel like I'm</i>
<i>in a fever dream,</i>

28:40.718 --> 28:42.137
<i>and I don't ever</i>
<i>want to wake up.</i>

28:42.220 --> 28:43.972
<i>Is this actually happening?</i>

28:44.055 --> 28:45.807
<i>PHIL:</i>
<i>It is happening, Annie.</i>

28:45.890 --> 28:47.642
<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>(giggles) There's a free table</i>

28:47.725 --> 28:48.977
<i>-by the end of the bar.</i>
-Oh.

28:49.060 --> 28:50.979
<i>PHIL:</i>
<i>Me, too. You face front.</i>

28:51.062 --> 28:52.147
{\an5}<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>So, what should we do</i>
<i>when we get there?</i>

28:52.230 --> 28:54.190
<i>PHIL: Well, I know</i>
<i>the first thing I'm gonna do.</i>

28:54.274 --> 28:56.651
<i>I am gonna run over to you</i>
<i>and I'm gonna pick you up</i>

28:56.734 --> 28:58.987
<i>in my arms and I'm gonna</i>
<i>give you the biggest kiss</i>

28:59.070 --> 29:00.822
<i>that you've ever gotten</i>
<i>in your whole damn life.</i>

29:00.905 --> 29:02.615
<i>ANNIE: Oh, you want to know</i>
<i>what I'm gonna do first thing?</i>

29:02.699 --> 29:05.118
-Excuse me, is this seat taken?
-Sorry, someone's sitting here.

29:05.201 --> 29:07.620
{\an5}<i>-PHIL: What?</i>
<i>-ANNIE: Call the cops</i>
<i>on this random dude</i>

29:07.704 --> 29:09.164
<i>who's all up in my face.</i>

29:09.247 --> 29:11.624
<i>No, I'm-I'm gonna kiss you</i>
<i>right back</i>

29:11.708 --> 29:13.334
<i>-and never let you go.</i>
<i>-Mm-hmm.</i>

29:13.418 --> 29:15.003
(music playing over earbuds)

29:15.086 --> 29:17.505
♪<i> So much it makes</i>
<i>you wanna cry now...</i> ♪

29:17.589 --> 29:19.299
<i>PHIL:</i>
<i>Oh, yeah, oh...</i>

29:19.382 --> 29:22.677
<i>Oh, my God, this...</i>
<i>second verse is my favorite!</i>

29:22.760 --> 29:24.721
<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>Oh, yeah, this is so good.</i>

29:24.804 --> 29:27.140
{\an5}<i>-PHIL: Oh, so good.</i>
<i>-Okay, I got to</i>
<i>confess something.</i>

29:27.223 --> 29:30.351
{\an5}<i>-PHIL: Okay.</i>
<i>-I kind of only listen</i>
<i>to show tunes.</i>

29:30.435 --> 29:32.187
{\an5}<i>-PHIL: Goddamn it, stop it.</i>
<i>Stop saying that to me.</i>
<i>-(laughs)</i>

29:32.270 --> 29:33.354
<i>-Why? What? They make me happy.</i>
<i>-Annie, what?</i>

29:33.438 --> 29:35.523
<i>All right, well, my lords,</i>

29:35.607 --> 29:37.817
<i>I'm just gonna have to</i>
<i>do something about that.</i>

29:37.901 --> 29:40.904
{\an5}<i>-I'll help you,</i>
<i>I'll-I'll show you the light.</i>
<i>-(laughs)</i>

29:40.987 --> 29:43.031
<i>Goddamn, Annie, I just...</i>

29:43.114 --> 29:46.701
<i>I have been searching for you</i>
<i>my whole life and...</i>

29:46.784 --> 29:48.203
<i>-ANNIE: Phil?</i>
<i>-Yeah?</i>

29:48.286 --> 29:50.705
{\an5}<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>There's a weird guy</i>
<i>staring at me.</i>

29:50.788 --> 29:52.999
{\an5}<i>PHIL:</i>
<i>Well, tell him to fuck off.</i>
<i>You're mine.</i>

29:53.082 --> 29:55.335
<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>No, he's...</i>

29:55.418 --> 29:57.045
<i>he's making me feel</i>
<i>super uneasy.</i>

29:57.128 --> 30:00.340
<i>I'm-- mm-- I'm gonna move</i>
<i>to another train car.</i>

30:00.423 --> 30:01.257
<i>PHIL:</i>
<i>Oh, are you serious?</i>

30:01.341 --> 30:02.884
<i>Annie, are there other people</i>
<i>around?</i>

30:02.967 --> 30:04.052
<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>Oh, my God, he's following me.</i>

30:04.135 --> 30:06.012
<i>He's sit...</i>

30:06.095 --> 30:08.556
<i>PHIL:</i>
<i>Annie. Annie, are you okay?</i>

30:08.640 --> 30:10.391
<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>He's sitting right next to me.</i>

30:10.475 --> 30:12.018
<i>PHIL:</i>
<i>Oh, my God, what a psycho.</i>

30:12.101 --> 30:14.062
<i>Um, okay, try not to worry.</i>

30:14.145 --> 30:16.689
<i>Annie, you're gonna be okay.</i>
<i>Hey, I'm here with you.</i>

30:16.773 --> 30:18.983
<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>But you're not really.</i>

30:19.067 --> 30:21.110
{\an5}<i>PHIL:</i>
<i>But I'm here with you</i>
<i>in your head.</i>

30:21.194 --> 30:23.571
<i>So just go somewhere safe,</i>
<i>okay?</i>

30:23.655 --> 30:25.406
<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>The train is stopped.</i>

30:25.490 --> 30:27.909
<i>I'm just-- I'm--</i>
<i>I'm gonna get off here, okay?</i>

30:27.992 --> 30:30.036
<i>I'm at the Kingswood Station,</i>
<i>so meet me there.</i>

30:30.119 --> 30:32.247
{\an5}<i>-Oh, my God, Phil!</i>
<i>-What? What-What-What's</i>
<i>going on?</i>

30:32.330 --> 30:33.831
<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>He got off the train, too!</i>

30:33.915 --> 30:35.792
<i>PHIL:</i>
<i>Um... hey, look for people.</i>

30:35.875 --> 30:37.460
<i>-ANNIE: There's nobody here!</i>
<i>-Okay.</i>

30:37.544 --> 30:39.295
<i>Stay calm, stay calm, stay--</i>
<i>Uh, keep moving.</i>

30:39.379 --> 30:40.922
<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>I'm behind this big horse.</i>

30:41.005 --> 30:42.131
<i>PHIL:</i>
<i>Horse? Horse? Where are you?</i>

30:42.215 --> 30:43.591
<i>-ANNIE: He's coming!</i>
<i>-Get out of there!</i>

30:43.675 --> 30:44.592
<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>There's a holiday market.</i>

30:44.676 --> 30:46.386
<i>-Should I make a run for it?</i>
<i>-Yeah, yeah.</i>

30:46.469 --> 30:47.929
<i>Just, uh, we'll do it together.</i>
<i>Are you ready?</i>

30:48.012 --> 30:49.764
<i>Three, two, go! Run! Annie, go!</i>

30:49.847 --> 30:51.224
<i>I'm with you.</i>
<i>I'm with you, baby.</i>

30:51.307 --> 30:53.601
♪ ♪

30:53.685 --> 30:55.478
<i>Annie, what's happening?</i>

30:55.562 --> 30:56.771
<i>Talk to me.</i>

30:56.854 --> 30:58.606
<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>Holy shit. Holy shit.</i>

30:58.690 --> 30:59.941
<i>-PHIL: Huh? What?</i>
<i>-I did it!</i>

31:00.024 --> 31:01.401
<i>I think I'm safe.</i>

31:01.484 --> 31:02.944
<i>There's, there's lots</i>
<i>of people here.</i>

31:03.027 --> 31:05.530
<i>-I... I think I lost him.</i>
<i>-Oh! Thank...</i>

31:08.825 --> 31:10.410
<i>-Thank God.</i>
<i>-ANNIE: Oh, my God. Whew!</i>

31:10.493 --> 31:12.120
<i>That was scary.</i>

31:12.203 --> 31:14.622
<i>Talk about an exciting start</i>
<i>to our trip, huh?</i>

31:14.706 --> 31:16.457
<i>-PHIL: Yeah, you think?</i>
<i>-Should I get you</i>

31:16.541 --> 31:18.251
<i>a Christmas gift</i>
<i>while I'm here?</i>

31:18.334 --> 31:20.461
<i>-PHIL: Yeah...</i>
<i>-Oh, God.</i>

31:20.545 --> 31:22.714
<i>I'm gonna go back to the--</i>
<i>Oh, my God. Oh, my God.</i>

31:22.797 --> 31:24.591
<i>-PHIL: What? What?</i>
<i>-Phil, he's here!</i>

31:24.674 --> 31:26.175
♪ ♪

31:26.259 --> 31:28.261
<i>-PHIL: Annie?</i>
<i>-(Annie screams)</i>

31:28.344 --> 31:31.264
Annie! Annie!

31:31.347 --> 31:32.932
Annie?

31:33.016 --> 31:34.475
<i>Annie? Annie?</i>

31:34.559 --> 31:37.312
Is everything all right?
You okay?

31:37.395 --> 31:40.607
Yeah... uh, yeah,
Kingswood. Kingswood.

31:40.690 --> 31:43.651
{\an5}-Sir?
-Kingswood. How long until
we get to the Kingswood Station?

31:43.735 --> 31:45.486
We arrive at 6:15.

31:45.570 --> 31:47.822
Four hours, man,
that's too much time. Um...

31:47.905 --> 31:49.699
Sir? You're going
to have to calm down,

31:49.782 --> 31:51.784
or I'll be throwing you off
at the next stop,

31:51.868 --> 31:54.162
{\an5}-and it'll be a lot longer
to Kingswood than that.
-Okay.

31:54.245 --> 31:55.997
-Sit down.
-Yeah.

31:56.080 --> 31:58.082
(panting):
I got it.

31:59.917 --> 32:01.419
Hey, hey.

32:03.421 --> 32:07.383
{\an8}<i>PHIL: Baby, if you can hear me,</i>
<i>I'm coming to save you.</i>

32:15.725 --> 32:17.393
{\an8}PHIL:
Excuse me. Excuse me.

32:17.477 --> 32:18.394
{\an8}WOMAN:
Excuse you.

32:18.478 --> 32:20.396
{\an8}MAN:
Watch it.

32:20.480 --> 32:22.231
{\an5}<i>MAN 2 (over P.A.):</i>
<i>Your attention,</i>
<i>your attention...</i>

32:22.315 --> 32:23.316
(baby crying)

32:23.399 --> 32:25.234
(indistinct chatter)

32:30.239 --> 32:32.408
Horse. Horse.

32:32.492 --> 32:34.869
Horse, horse. Um...

32:35.912 --> 32:37.372
Market.

32:37.455 --> 32:41.042
(gasps)
Okay, okay!

32:41.125 --> 32:42.752
Hold on, baby!

32:42.835 --> 32:44.879
(panting)

32:50.134 --> 32:53.888
Hey, hey! Wait.
Please. Wait, please!

32:53.971 --> 32:55.598
-Please, please. Wait.
-(engine starts)

32:55.682 --> 32:58.226
Wait, have you seen this woman?
Have you seen this woman?

32:58.309 --> 32:59.560
Have you seen this woman,
please?

32:59.644 --> 33:00.937
-Wait, wait, wait!
-(tires screeching)

33:03.815 --> 33:05.525
(glass cracks)

33:13.032 --> 33:15.618
No, no, no, no, no, no.

33:15.702 --> 33:19.539
(fading):
No, no, no, no, no, no, no.

33:19.622 --> 33:22.291
No, no, no, no, no!

33:22.375 --> 33:24.419
(panting)

33:27.213 --> 33:29.257
(crying)

33:39.058 --> 33:41.060
<i>-ANNIE: Phil?</i>
-Annie?

33:41.144 --> 33:43.604
Annie? Annie, oh, my God,
you're alive. Are you okay?

33:43.688 --> 33:46.274
-Where are you?
<i>-I-I came to...</i>

33:46.357 --> 33:49.944
<i>and it's dark</i>
<i>and it smells musty.</i>

33:50.027 --> 33:51.988
Baby, I'm in Kingswood, I've
been looking all over for you.

33:52.071 --> 33:54.115
I have your glasses. Um...

33:54.198 --> 33:55.992
You got to give me something--
okay, just anything, so I can,

33:56.075 --> 33:59.328
so I can find you-- uh, sights
or sounds or-or smells, please.

33:59.412 --> 34:00.788
<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>I think I'm in the woods.</i>

34:00.872 --> 34:03.124
<i>I hear an owl in the distance?</i>

34:03.207 --> 34:05.126
An owl. An owl.

34:05.209 --> 34:07.128
-An owl.
-(distant hooting)

34:07.211 --> 34:09.213
(panting)

34:14.719 --> 34:17.263
♪ ♪

34:17.346 --> 34:19.348
(hooting continues)

34:33.696 --> 34:35.697
(creatures screeching)

34:39.744 --> 34:41.788
(hooting)

34:59.597 --> 35:01.891
(man speaking indistinctly
on TV)

35:12.276 --> 35:14.278
(banging on door)

35:22.078 --> 35:24.121
Yeah?

35:24.205 --> 35:26.874
Any other houses
in this area, man?

35:26.958 --> 35:28.668
You're looking at it.

35:28.751 --> 35:31.504
{\an5}-Yeah?
-Can I help you
with something, pal?

35:32.672 --> 35:34.715
Yeah, perhaps you can, pal.

35:37.468 --> 35:39.428
You hiding anything back there?

35:39.512 --> 35:41.430
-What are you talking about?
-Yeah...

35:41.514 --> 35:45.434
Was there a woman-- was there
a woman in this area tonight?

35:45.518 --> 35:47.103
What the hell are you doing

35:47.186 --> 35:48.729
on my porch
in the middle of the night?

35:48.813 --> 35:51.524
How about you just answer
my question, asshole?

35:51.607 --> 35:55.736
You get the hell out of here
or I'm calling the cops.

35:55.820 --> 35:59.198
Call 'em. Call the cops.
Call 'em.

35:59.282 --> 36:01.576
<i>Annie, Annie, did the man</i>
<i>who took you have a beard?</i>

36:01.659 --> 36:03.244
<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>Yes! Yes, he did!</i>

36:03.327 --> 36:04.871
<i>And a-a plaid shirt!</i>

36:04.954 --> 36:06.831
Motherfucker.

36:08.040 --> 36:09.876
(yelling)

36:09.959 --> 36:10.960
Where is she?!

36:22.638 --> 36:25.057
{\an8}(woman speaking indistinctly
on TV)

36:25.141 --> 36:26.559
-Where is she?!
-(grunts)

36:26.642 --> 36:28.895
Where is she?!

36:45.828 --> 36:47.830
(panting)

37:05.640 --> 37:07.183
I-I'm sorry.

37:07.266 --> 37:08.517
I'm-I'm sorry.

37:08.601 --> 37:11.145
<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>Phil, are you still here?</i>

37:11.228 --> 37:12.396
Yeah.

37:12.480 --> 37:13.981
<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>You got quiet.</i>

37:23.783 --> 37:25.826
GIRL:
Daddy?

37:32.250 --> 37:36.587
(TV playing indistinctly)

37:36.671 --> 37:38.965
ANNIE:
Audra, where are you?

37:39.048 --> 37:40.633
Honey, what are you doing?

37:40.716 --> 37:43.678
You know you need to go to bed.
Come on. Come on, let's go.

37:43.761 --> 37:46.389
Annie. Hey, it's me.

37:47.723 --> 37:49.725
Who are you?

37:52.395 --> 37:54.730
-Annie.
-What are you doing here?

37:55.898 --> 37:57.316
♪<i> You're just too good</i> ♪

37:57.400 --> 37:58.526
-♪<i> To be true...</i> ♪
-Oh, my God!

37:58.609 --> 38:00.277
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

38:00.361 --> 38:02.822
-What did you do to my husband?
-No, no, no, hey, hey, hey, hey.

38:02.905 --> 38:06.200
No, no, no, it's-it's me, it's
Phil. It's Phil from Ashford.

38:06.283 --> 38:07.868
You know, we were
gonna meet halfway

38:07.952 --> 38:09.912
in-in Pilson Bay, and then...

38:09.996 --> 38:14.709
Um, and then, uh,
I got off the train and, uh...

38:14.792 --> 38:16.877
-and I got your glasses.
-AUDRA: Mom?

38:16.961 --> 38:19.046
{\an5}-You needed me
to save your life.
-I'm scared.

38:19.130 --> 38:21.966
Stay away. You stay away!
Stay away from us.

38:22.049 --> 38:23.676
-No. No, what-what, hey, please.
-No, don't come any closer. No--

38:23.759 --> 38:25.511
-Stay right there! Stay...
-AUDRA: Mom, I'm scared.

38:25.594 --> 38:26.387
No, but you needed me to save...

38:26.470 --> 38:28.889
-Annie? Just wait...
-Get away from us.

38:28.973 --> 38:30.224
{\an5}-Run to your room
and close the door.
-AUDRA: Mommy...

38:30.307 --> 38:32.101
{\an5}-Please, Annie.
-(Audra screams)
-No.

38:32.184 --> 38:33.561
Don't come any closer to me.

38:33.644 --> 38:34.895
I just saved your life!

38:34.979 --> 38:36.397
I just saved
your life.

38:36.480 --> 38:38.315
-Freeze! Show me your hands.
-What?

38:38.399 --> 38:40.276
{\an5}-You, sir,
hands where I can see them.
-No...

38:40.359 --> 38:41.736
-Freeze.
-Don't move.

38:41.819 --> 38:43.112
Wh-What is happening?

38:43.195 --> 38:44.280
He broke into my house!

38:44.363 --> 38:46.574
{\an5}-What?
-OFFICER: Sir...
-OFFICER 2: Get on the ground!

38:46.657 --> 38:50.119
No. Just-just wait.
Just wait. Hey... (grunts)

38:50.202 --> 38:52.121
Annie-- No! Hey, ow!

38:52.204 --> 38:54.206
You don't understand,
she was in danger!

38:54.290 --> 38:57.084
<i>Annie, can you hear me?!</i>
<i>Say something! Please!</i>

38:57.168 --> 38:59.587
{\an5}ANNIE:
I don't know who he is!
I've never seen him before.

38:59.670 --> 39:01.047
He broke into my house
and he attacked my husband.

39:01.130 --> 39:02.757
-Why-- why are you saying that?
-Please help me!

39:02.840 --> 39:04.884
-He attacked my husband!
-We've been talking for weeks.

39:04.967 --> 39:07.595
-No!
-Tell them about Pilson Bay.

39:07.678 --> 39:09.722
(Phil shouting)

39:12.183 --> 39:15.728
♪<i> Oh, pretty baby, now that</i>
<i>I've found you, stay</i> ♪

39:15.811 --> 39:17.772
♪<i> And let me love you, baby...</i> ♪

39:17.855 --> 39:20.816
Annie! Annie!

39:20.900 --> 39:22.943
♪<i> Love you...</i> ♪

39:23.027 --> 39:24.987
{\an5}OFFICER:
You want to take this psychopath
down to the station,

39:25.071 --> 39:26.155
or should I?

39:26.238 --> 39:27.573
He's all yours.

39:27.656 --> 39:29.658
(chuckles)
You owe me.

39:36.457 --> 39:38.459
Oh, my God.

39:39.543 --> 39:42.797
Oh, my God.

39:42.880 --> 39:44.757
Oh, my-- She's right.

39:46.759 --> 39:48.385
My shrink's right, I'm...

39:49.386 --> 39:51.305
I hear voices.

39:51.388 --> 39:54.141
(laughs)

39:54.225 --> 39:55.893
I hear voices.

39:57.478 --> 39:59.355
I...

39:59.438 --> 40:04.276
I traveled halfway across
the country for nobody.

40:04.360 --> 40:06.112
I killed a random guy!

40:06.195 --> 40:08.823
I just, just bashed his face in.

40:08.906 --> 40:10.950
(crying)

40:13.244 --> 40:16.080
I killed a guy.

40:16.163 --> 40:19.333
And his daughter,
and his poor daughter.

40:19.416 --> 40:21.252
(sobs)

40:21.335 --> 40:23.420
It's just me.

40:23.504 --> 40:26.841
I'm a murderer.
Oh, I'm a murderer.

40:26.924 --> 40:29.301
It's all me. It was just me.

40:29.385 --> 40:31.178
Oh, my God!

40:31.262 --> 40:32.888
(moaning):
Oh...

40:34.932 --> 40:37.226
<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>Hello, Phil.</i>

40:37.309 --> 40:39.311
<i>-PHIL: Annie?</i>
<i>-ANNIE: Oh, God,</i>

40:39.395 --> 40:42.398
<i>I've been waiting</i>
<i>for this day for a long time.</i>

40:42.481 --> 40:45.192
{\an5}<i>-PHIL: What?</i>
<i>-ANNIE: I told you</i>
<i>it was complicated.</i>

40:45.276 --> 40:47.153
<i>PHIL:</i>
<i>What are you talking about?</i>

40:47.236 --> 40:48.821
{\an5}<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>This was about a better future</i>
<i>for me and Audra.</i>

40:48.904 --> 40:50.573
Thank you so much.

40:50.656 --> 40:52.032
{\an5}<i>PHIL:</i>
<i>I don't understand.</i>
<i>What are you...</i>

40:52.116 --> 40:53.409
<i>What is happening here?</i>

40:53.492 --> 40:56.412
<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>You were my escape hatch, Phil.</i>

40:56.495 --> 40:58.998
<i>You saved us.</i>

40:59.081 --> 41:04.044
<i>Now my life can finally begin,</i>
<i>all because of you.</i>

41:04.128 --> 41:06.255
<i>PHIL:</i>
<i>No. No. No.</i>

41:06.338 --> 41:08.048
<i>Oh, my God, you are a monster.</i>

41:08.132 --> 41:11.552
<i>You-- You're-- you lied to me!</i>

41:11.635 --> 41:14.930
<i>ANNIE:</i>
<i>No, not really.</i>

41:15.014 --> 41:18.392
<i>All I ever did was tell you</i>
<i>what you wanted to hear,</i>

41:18.475 --> 41:21.937
<i>and you were willing</i>
<i>to kill for it.</i>

41:22.021 --> 41:26.066
<i>I told you, you had a purpose.</i>

41:26.150 --> 41:28.152
<i>Goodbye, Phil.</i>

41:30.321 --> 41:32.198
No, oh, no!

41:32.281 --> 41:33.908
NARRATOR:
What kind of compromise goes

41:33.991 --> 41:36.243
into connecting
with another human being?

41:36.327 --> 41:38.078
Is it meeting in the middle?

41:38.162 --> 41:41.582
Or going all the way
to the end of the line?

41:41.665 --> 41:43.417
Philip Hayes found connection

41:43.500 --> 41:47.213
but only with the darkest part
of his soul.

41:47.296 --> 41:49.048
A region of self
that he'll inhabit

41:49.131 --> 41:50.925
for the rest of his life.

41:51.008 --> 41:54.261
Here, in The Twilight Zone.

